%20working%20on%20a%20bag%20of%20blood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c8417ef9db348adc0b7c52%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223940%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Etk%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Sean%20Ferry%2C%20114th%20Public%20Affairs%20Detachment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20US%20Army%20exercise%20looked%20at%20life-saving%20medical%20care%20when%20wounded%20troops%20can't%20be%20flown%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20an%20intense%20conflict%2C%20getting%20troops%20off%20the%20field%20or%20bringing%20in%20supplies%20could%20prove%20extremely%20difficult.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20exercise%20revived%20the%20%26quot%3Bwalking%20blood%20bank%26quot%3B%20concept%20from%20World%20War%20I%2C%20using%20soldiers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWestern%20troops%20may%20face%20deadlier%20fights%20in%20future%20wars.%20If%20helicopters%20can't%20fly%20medevac%20flights%2C%20the%20US%20Army's%20fallback%20for%20treating%20the%20wounded%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F15-photos-from-world-war-i-veterans-day-armistice-anniversary-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWorld%20War%20I%3C%2Fa%3E%20approach%3A%20using%20soldiers%20as%20%26quot%3Bwalking%20blood%20banks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20recent%20exercise%20on%20a%20German%20hillside%2C%20the%20Army%20and%20its%20allies%20and%20partners%20simulated%20enemy%20artillery%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efire%20that%20resulted%20in%20tremendous%20soldier%20casualties.%20Without%20air%20superiority%20for%20flying%20evacuations%20for%20the%20injured%20or%20bringing%20in%20needed%20supplies%2C%20life-saving%20treatment%20had%20to%20be%20done%20right%20near%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFront-line%20Army%20medical%20personnel%20practiced%20an%20old%20tactic%20making%20a%20comeback%2C%20with%20troops%20lining%20up%20to%20give%20blood%20directly%20to%20the%20wounded%20right%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20this%20situation%2C%20blood%20transfusions%20were%20done%20with%20donations%20from%20soldiers%20who%20were%20pre-screened%20and%20prepared%20to%20donate%20blood%20on%20the%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exercise%20saw%20US%20soldiers%20from%20the%202nd%20Cavalry%20Regiment%20and%201st%20Armored%20Division%20Combat%20Aviation%20Brigade%20training%20to%20provide%20prolonged%20care%20in%20the%20field%2C%20a%20necessity%20in%20situations%20like%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20or%20potential%20future%20conflicts%2C%20where%20contested%20air%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20move%20injured%20troops%20off%20the%20battlefield%20for%20trauma%20care%20in%20the%20critical%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-warned-golden-hour-save-soldiers-threatened-russia-ukraine-lost-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egolden%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20window.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20were%20able%20to%20enjoy%20that%20during%20the%20conflicts%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20that%20might%20not%20be%20an%20option%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20military%20personnel%20wearing%20camouflage%20stand%20around%20in%20a%20medical%20tent.%20A%20man%20lies%20on%20a%20stretcher%20receiving%20simulated%20medical%20attention%20during%20an%20exercise.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c857d457d362d375e82f26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETK%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Sean%20Ferry%2C%20114th%20Public%20Affairs%20Detachment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20looking%20to%20do%20is%20to%20try%20and%20exercise%20the%20delivery%20of%20giving%20blood%2C%20in%20a%20far%20forward%20situation%2C%20from%20our%20own%20organic%20sources%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Maj.%20Cat%20Kemeny%2C%20the%20regimental%20medical%20officer%20with%204%20Regiment%20Army%20Air%20Corps%2C%20British%20Army%2C%20per%20a%20US%20Army%20release.%20%26quot%3BThose%20organic%20sources%20are%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKemeny%20said%20that%20troops%20are%20an%20ideal%20source%20because%20the%20blood%20is%20stored%20at%20a%20perfect%20temperature%20in%20their%20bodies%20and%20makes%20for%20a%20quick%20transfusion%20with%20no%20degradation%20due%20to%20time%20or%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20blood%20banks%20aren't%20a%20new%20concept%2C%20having%20originated%20during%20World%20War%20I%20when%20transporting%20injured%20soldiers%20for%20life-saving%20treatment%20couldn't%20be%20done%20quickly%20enough.%20The%20approach%20has%20been%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bbuddy%20transfusion%26quot%3B%20or%20direct%20donor-to-patient%20transfusion%20and%20was%20pioneered%20during%20WWI.%20Although%20it%20fell%20out%20of%20practice%20decades%20ago%20due%20to%20safety%20concerns%2C%20it's%20now%20possible%20again%20thanks%20to%20blood%20screening%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20necessitated%20by%20concerns%20that%20in%20a%20future%20war%2C%20evacuations%20and%20blood%20supplies%20on%20the%20battlefield%20could%20be%20disrupted%20by%20an%20adversary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-air-force-rethink-achieving-air-superiority-in-war-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtesting%20the%20airspace%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20making%20transporting%20critical%20supplies%20perilous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20recent%20training%20exercise%2C%20personnel%20were%20screened%20to%20determine%20blood-type%20matches%20or%20any%20disqualifying%20diseases.%20Once%20approved%2C%20they%20were%20taken%20to%20a%20medical%20tent%20to%20donate.%20The%20training%20transfusions%20took%20only%20minutes%20and%20resulted%20in%20a%20fresh%20supply%20of%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20wearing%20camouflage%20sits%20donating%20blood.%20Two%20people%20wearing%20camouflage%20stand%20next%20to%20her.%20They%20are%20all%20in%20a%20medical%20tent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c8581a57d362d375e82f2c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224045%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETK%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Sean%20Ferry%2C%20114th%20Public%20Affairs%20Detachment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKemeny%20said%20that%20while%20the%20walking%20blood%20bank%20was%20something%20done%20previously%2C%20it%20is%20still%20innovative%20since%20it%20had%20been%20out%20of%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Army%20has%20been%20reexamining%20the%20role%20of%20%26quot%3Bwalking%20blood%20banks%26quot%3B%20in%20battle%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%202019%2C%20the%20XVII%20Airborne%20Corps%20and%20Armed%20Services%20Blood%20Program%20partnered%20to%20identify%20soldiers%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.army.mil%2Farticle%2F224502%2Fwalking_blood_banks_fill_gap_for_medical_care_in_field_environment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniversal%20blood%20type%20O%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20could%20become%20immediate%20donors%20on%20the%20battlefield.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20could%20save%20lives%2C%20especially%20in%20remote%20locations%20where%20every%20second%20to%20treat%20wounded%20soldiers%20counts%2C%20personnel%20said%20at%20the%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20other%20experiments%20as%20well.%20In%20early%202024%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Army%20medics%20participating%20in%20a%20large-scale%20joint%20exercise%20in%20Alaska%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20the%20difficulties%20of%20treating%20injuries%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-us-army-is-training-soldiers-to-fight-in-arctic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecold-weather%20environments%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20the%20Arctic.%20Blood%20transfusions%20in%20particular%20were%20complicated%20by%20the%20low%20temperatures%2C%20leading%20personnel%20to%20experiment%20with%20walking%20blood%20banks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20a%20Danish-Ukrainian%20initiative%20is%20mobilizing%20a%20%26quot%3Bwalking%20blood%20bank%26quot%3B%20that%20taps%20both%20civilians%20and%20soldiers%20as%20donors.%20The%20program%20helps%20offset%20severe%20blood%20shortages%20caused%20by%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20which%20has%20driven%20up%20demand%20from%20mass%20casualties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20the%20return%20of%20walking%20blood%20banks%20as%20a%20concept%20is%20a%20clear%20reminder%20that%20future%20conflicts%20may%20demand%20not%20just%20new%20weapons%2C%20but%20also%20old%20practices%20reborn%20to%20keep%20soldiers%20alive%20when%20the%20skies%20aren't%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-reviving-wwi-walking-blood-bank-practice-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757968532000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c84198f9db348adc0b7c59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-reviving-wwi-walking-blood-bank-practice-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Without%20the%20ability%20to%20freely%20evacuate%20casualties%20or%20transport%20supplies%20via%20air%2C%20blood%20transfusions%20right%20on%20the%20battlefield%20could%20be%20critical.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A65%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-reviving-wwi-walking-blood-bank-practice-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ileana%20feels%20Ranbir%20was%20UNAWARE%20of%20THIS%20while%20shooting%20'Barfi'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%